2022.title: Lyricsum
2022.description: Lyricsum is a new way to generate placeholder text. It takes the lyrics of your favorite artists' songs and converts them into placeholder text which can be further customized.

2022.title: Codr
2022.description: CLI tool to help start your coding projects. It allows users to create new projects of varying technologies, view older projects, and search for projects using a specific command for each.

2022.title: Mapcident
2022.description: An app that uses the phone's accelerometer to detect accidents and crashes. It also allows users to see active accident sites near them so that they can go over to the specific location to provide aid.

2021.title: Markrate
2021.description: A platform that incentivizes its users with redeemable credits for promoting local businesses with fewer reviews on their social media handles.

2021.title: Konnect
2021.description: Konnect aims to make it easy to find people to work with on your tech projects. It solves the problem of finding people to collaborate with on personal projects, something which professional networking platforms fail to do.

2021.title: Encryptid '21
2021.description: The platform for Encryptid 2021, built with Express.js, Node.js, and MongoDB.

2021.title: CoDiff
2021.description: CoDiff is a VSCode extension that has live access to all your teammates' local changes, greatly improving communication: it notifies you of conflicts with teammates as they occur.

2021.title: COVICoin
2021.description: COVICoin is a gamified experience that gives users redeemable credits based on how many people they help. The system shows users specific tweets which are asking for leads about COVID resources.

2021.title: COVID-19 Bot
2021.description: A Twitter bot that automatically replies to tweets requesting COVID related resources with links containing information about the availability.

2021.title: Local Party
2021.description: A website where you can create rooms and chat while watching local video files synchronized with your friends.

2021.title: StarHub
2021.description: A chrome extension that tracks your GitHub stars so you don't have to.

2021.title: Know your traveller
2021.description: A mobile app connecting travellers and travelling agencies for seamless and safer post-COVID travel.

2020.title: VSCode DMs
2020.description: Direct Messages is a simple way of messaging your developer friends and collaborating with them through VSCode.

2020.title: Codimg
2020.description: A re-modelled approach to plagiarism detection which enables software owners to generate a report for themselves on where, how and what piece of code written by them has been used by developers around the world.

2020.title: Lancerate
2020.description: A crowdsourced verification system for freelancers to know the ideal amount they should charge for their services.

2020.title: Encryptid '20
2020.description: The platform for Encryptid '20 cryptic hunt built using Django, PostgreSQL, and Firestore.
